    {
      "id": 116757671,
      "date": "2026-07-29",
      "name": "BENCHMARK \u2014 VLamax Substrate Re-test (Z2 FatMax)",
      "type": "Ride",
      "planned_tss": null,
      "duration_hours": 2.0,
      "duration_formatted": "2h00m",
      "description": "CONTROLLED RE-TEST of the Jun 17 baseline. Goal: track modeled carb burn (intervals.icu CHO Used) at identical power as a real-world proxy for VLamax change. Baseline = 201g CHO over 1h56 (~104 g/hr) at 132W avg.\n\nSTRUCTURE:\n- 10:00 60-62% FTP (warmup ~145W)\n- 1:42:00 54-57% FTP (MAIN \u2014 hold 130-135W steady, HARD CAP 145W/FatMax, VI < 1.05, NO surges)\n- 5:00 25-45% FTP (cooldown)\n\nCONTROLS (must match baseline or the comparison is meaningless):\n1. POWER: 130-135W avg, NP ~137. Same as baseline.\n2. DURATION: 2:00 exactly.\n3. CONDITIONS: indoor Zwift, 2 fans, same room, late-afternoon start (~4pm).\n4. FUELING: water/electrolytes only on the bike, NO carbs. Standardized pre-ride state (fasted or one fixed light breakfast). Keep IDENTICAL every re-test.\n5. CADENCE: ~87 rpm.\n6. FTP SETTING: must be 240W in intervals.icu for this ride. If FTP has changed, note it \u2014 the CHO model is FTP-driven and a different FTP shifts the estimate at the same watts.\n\nAFTER: record CHO Used, Calories, avg power, avg HR, Pw:Hr decoupling. Falling CHO/hr at the same power+HR = VLamax trending down toward the 0.35 goal."
    },
